  "summary": "Moira Nicholson questions Bobbie Jones about his connection to the police. Bobbie, who has been posing as a chauffeur named Higgins for Frankie DeWinter, explains that he needs to find Frankie quickly and instructs Moira to arrange a meeting at a river pavilion. Before departing, Bobbie speaks with Mr. Eschew at an inn, making a casual comment about Mrs. Nicholson to avoid drawing suspicion toward her that might reach Dr. Nicholson.\n\nAt the pavilion, Bobbie reveals his true identity to Moira. He informs her that her friend, Allen Castles, died on October 3rd after falling off a cliff in Marchbault, noting that Castles had been carrying a photograph of Moira in his pocket. While Moira is saddened, she does not reveal that she knew of his death. When Bobbie asks if she knows anyone named Evans, she denies it.\n\nFrankie arrives to join the group, and the three discuss the ongoing investigation. Frankie clarifies the circumstances surrounding Bobbie's recent ordeal, noting that after an inquest involving the Kemman couple, Bobbie was targeted with eight morphine pills in his beer following his refusal of a suspicious job offer. The group deduces that Allen Castles was pushed off the cliff rather than falling accidentally. They identify Roger Baskin-Fontaine as the prime suspect because he was present at the scene and possessed the photograph of Moira. Frankie admits she staged a car accident to bring Bobbie to the area to investigate. Although Moira fears her husband, Jasper, is a suspect, Bobbie reassures her that they had not heard of him until their arrival. Frankie clarifies that their primary focus is now on Roger Baskin-Fontaine.",
